  "texts": [
    "This step focuses the analysis on more meaningful terms that are likely to contribute to distinguishing spam from legitimate messages.",
    "5) Stemming: Stemming algorithms were applied to the text to reduce words to their root forms.",
    "This allows the model to recognize different variations of a word as the same entity, improving the model's ability to generalize from the training data.",
    "6) Vectorization: Finally, the processed text was vectorized, transforming it into numerical data that can be effectively processed by machine learning algorithms.Techniques such as Term Frequency-Inverse Document Frequency (TF-IDF) were employed to highlight the importance of specific terms within the emails, based on their frequency across the dataset and their uniqueness to individual messages.",
    "These preprocessing steps are integral to the preparation of the SpamAssassin dataset for spam detection analysis."
